              <h3>Caleb</h3>
              <p>Creating and sharing nutrient-dense, neo-traditional, and (usually) delicious meals with friends, family, and my community is a deep passion of mine. Much aligned with my musical tastes, I love to cook with complex and aggressive flavor profiles from all corners of the globe. My best dishes are labors of love… and are almost always topped with few dashes of homemade hot sauce! I love to explore and experience rich flavors and aromas, whether that’s coming from home-cooked feasts or a decadent craft beer or cocktail.</p>
              <p>Studying and incorporating regenerative agriculture and organic gardening into my life has been richly rewarding and I don’t see myself turning back. I’m a professional restoration ecologist, permaculturist, and tree nerd, and I also dabble in edible & medicinal plant and mushroom foraging. My wife (Rossi) and I have an increasingly productive suburban homestead & wildlife habitat here in Northern Virginia, where we host our semi-annual Feasts.</p>
              <p>I don’t care for politics, but I do strongly believe that supporting local, values-based businesses is the only solution to shifting our globalized, profit-driven economy into something that truly supports both our planet and our people. For me, a worthy cause is sticking it to The Man and overhauling how we (humanity) feed ourselves...with no compromises on deliciousness! At essence, I’m a huge nerd and animal lover, and I strive to walk the walk when it comes to compassionate, healthy, and sustainable living \m/</p>
            </div>
